00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:28.289
A clothing store in Japan has a hanger system
that displays video of a model wearing the

00:00:28.289 --> 00:00:33.039
clothes you remove from the rack. The hangers
have simple on/off switches depending on if

00:00:33.039 --> 00:00:38.290
the article of clothing is hanging or is picked
up, and each have a unique ID that is tied

00:00:38.290 --> 00:00:44.480
to a PC in the back which displays a photo
or video of the model wearing that piece of

00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:48.890
clothing. It's kind of a digital take on mannequins,
but it's more of a novelty to try and get

00:00:48.890 --> 00:00:52.370
online shoppers back into brick and mortar stores.

00:00:52.370 --> 00:00:58.200
These LED ice cubes let you know when you've
had too much alcohol. Developed by an MIT

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:03.540
Media Lab researcher, the edible gelatin ice
cubes hold a coin cell battery, a microcontroller,

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:08.990
and a transceiver to track the number of sips
and total time drinking. They flash in sync

00:01:08.990 --> 00:01:14.299
with ambient music, and change color to represent
the levels of intoxication.

00:01:14.299 --> 00:01:19.310
Aspire Bariatrics has developed a system that
allows people to lose weight by emptying their

00:01:19.310 --> 00:01:25.409
stomach with a valve after a meal. Aspiration
Therapy involves a tube in the stomach connected

00:01:25.409 --> 00:01:30.569
to a Skin-Port that can be opened to empty
stomach contents before they pass into the

00:01:30.569 --> 00:01:35.869
intestines where the calories are absorbed.
And then you just dump the stuff in the toilet...So,

00:01:35.869 --> 00:01:36.719
yeah...

