00:01:42.950 --> 00:01:49.130
VELOCIRoACH is the second fastest legged robot,
clocking in at 3.2 meters per second. It moves

00:01:49.130 --> 00:01:53.579
like a real cockroach with its legs
hitting the ground 15 times per second, and

00:01:53.579 --> 00:01:59.929
the cardboard roach can move 26 times its
body length in only one second, and also can

00:01:59.929 --> 00:02:02.149
carry four times its weight.

00:02:02.149 --> 00:02:08.179
Diego San is a humanoid robot toddler that
combines advancements in robotics, neuroscience,

00:02:08.179 --> 00:02:13.200
computer vision, developmental psychology
and machine learning. Developed at the University

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:18.450
of California, San Diego, it mimics the expressions
of a one-year-old child, and the plan is to

00:02:18.450 --> 00:02:23.060
use it in studies on sensory-motor and social
development- basically, how babies learn to

00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:26.100
control their bodies and interact with others.

00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:32.290
The Power Loader Power Amplification Exoskeleton
Robot is being developed by Panasonic subsidiary,

00:02:32.290 --> 00:02:39.290
Activelink. It's a full body exoskeleton designed
to carry over 220lbs, and they hope to use

00:02:39.810 --> 00:02:45.700
a more compact version for use in the reconstruction
of the Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant.

